### New Connections Identified (Run 3)

- **GSDMC/Pyroptosis bridge** (HIGH-VALUE, PENDING CONFIRMATION): GSDMC is #1 SHAP feature in anti-TNF classifier. Gasdermins execute pyroptosis → IL-1β release. IL1B massively upregulated in non-responders (logFC=3858). Hypothesis: epithelial pyroptosis drives a non-response subtype. BLOCKED: anti-TNF pipeline must be re-run with leakage fix before GSDMC finding can be trusted.
- **Fibrotic non-response STRENGTHENED**: ILK (fibroblast/ECM, stability=0.795) confirmed in anti-TNF 30-gene signature. Th17 pathway completely absent. 2/30 genes map to fibrosis/ECM.
- **CD38/NAD+ metabolic bridge**: Convergent signal across fibrosis (transition_signature), anti-TNF (NAMPT), and microbiome (Tryptophan-NAD axis). Daratumumab/isatuximab ranked #7-8 as fibrosis drug candidates. Very speculative.
- **Th17 absence**: Anti-TNF non-responder phenotype = innate immunity + epithelial dysfunction + fibrosis, NOT Th17/adaptive. Implications for IL-23 atlas and treatment sequencing.

